{"id":232173,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sam_Harris","text":"Samuel Benjamin Harris (born April 9, 1967) is an American author. He is a philosopher, neuroscientist, atheist and humanist. He is the co-founder and CEO of Project Reason.\nHarris, Christopher Hitchens, Richard Dawkins, and Daniel Dennett are commonly known as the \"Four Horsemen of Atheism\".","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":50},{"uri":"Author","surface_form":"author","offset":59},{"uri":"Philosopher","surface_form":"philosopher","offset":75},{"uri":"Neuroscientist","surface_form":"neuroscientist","offset":88},{"uri":"Atheist","surface_form":"atheist","offset":104},{"uri":"Humanist","surface_form":"humanist","offset":116},{"uri":"Chief_executive_officer","surface_form":"CEO","offset":151},{"uri":"Project_Reason","surface_form":"Project Reason","offset":158},{"uri":"Christopher_Hitchens","surface_form":"Christopher Hitchens","offset":182},{"uri":"Richard_Dawkins","surface_form":"Richard Dawkins","offset":204},{"uri":"Daniel_Dennett","surface_form":"Daniel Dennett","offset":225}]}